cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the optimization of fronthauling cost in C-RAN, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of genetic algorithms and fitness functions indicates that it could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
